From police nyalas stationed outside taxi ranks to passengers being searched before they go on their journeys, safety has become a huge concern in this industry. Last week, two taxi drivers were shot and killed at a taxi rank in Johannesburg as they were about to transport passengers. eNCA's Slindelo Masikane reports. #DStv403 PRETORIA - Fearing for their lives. That's how taxi drivers are feeling. This comes after two more drivers were shot and killed in full view of passengers recently. The SA National Taxi Council says this brings the number of taxi operator murders in the last six months to 13. WATCH: Taxi Violence | Santaco activates peace force forum It has now launched a 'peace force' team in an attempt to end the killings. Santaco says it has picked up a trend where drivers are being targeted at taxi ranks. * eNCA's Slindelo Masikane reports.